Perimeter security protects organizational boundaries from external attacks.

Real-life examples:

* Firewalls protecting public-facing servers
* DDoS mitigation for websites
* Web Application Firewalls for e-commerce apps
* Geo-blocking malicious regions

For example, online banking websites use WAFs to prevent web attacks.

A real-life use case is SaaS companies defending APIs.

Another example is streaming services mitigating DDoS attacks.

Perimeter security reduces exposure to internet-based threats.
